In this article, President Trump is asked about his remark regarding "no DACA deal." He responds by saying that Mexico needs to help the United States at the border, and if they don't, it's a sad situation between the two countries. He mentions that many people are coming in because they want to take advantage of DACA, and the Democrats had a chance to address this issue but failed to do so. He emphasizes that Mexico needs to stop allowing people to flow through their country and into the United States.